  "prompt": "How can I check if my iPhone is being tracked?",
  "response": "Here are some ways to check if your iPhone might be tracked:\n\n1. Check for unknown apps\n- Look for unfamiliar tracking or location-sharing apps\n- Review app permissions in Settings > Privacy\n\n2. Examine location services\n- Go to Settings > Privacy > Location Services\n- Check which apps have location access\n- Look for suspicious background app tracking\n\n3. Check Find My iPhone settings\n- Go to Settings > [Your Name] > Find My\n- Verify devices linked to your account\n- Remove any unknown devices\n\n4. Look for signs of unauthorized access\n- Check Apple ID login history\n- Review device list in iCloud settings\n- Change passwords if suspicious activity is found\n\n5. Physical signs of potential tracking\n- Unexpected battery drain\n- Strange background noise during calls\n- Phone heating up when not in use\n\n6. Use anti-spyware apps\n- Download reputable security apps\n- Run comprehensive device scans\n\n7. Advanced steps\n- Reset iPhone and restore from backup\n- Update iOS to latest version\n- Check for jailbreaking\n\n8. Professional assistance\n- Contact Apple Support\n- Visit an Apple Store for professional inspection\n\nIf you strongly suspect tracking, consider consulting cybersecurity professionals for thorough investigation.",
